  "doc_id": "23762",
  "text": "During the maintenance phase of replication, HPV genomes are replicated in S-phase in synchrony with host DNA replication. Cells containing HPV genomes have increased markers of ATM and ATR signaling, but pharmacological inhibition of the ATM pathway does not affect genome maintenance [CITATION_1] . However, it has been reported that siRNA-mediated reduction of ATM, ATR or several other proteins in the DDR pathway, as well as Chk1 inhibition results in 40%-50% reduction in HPV16 copy number in W12 cells [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
